FBIS4-50378 "drchi096_f_94005" FBIS-CHI-94-096 Daily Report 14 May 1994 Near East & South Asia Nepali Police Delegation Leaves Kathmandu for Beijing Nepali Police Delegation Leaves Kathmandu for Beijing OW1405105894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0905 GMT 14 May 94 OW1405105894 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Kathmandu, May 14 (XINHUA) -- A four-member Nepali police delegation left here this afternoon for China for a one-week visit at invitation of the Chinese Ministry of Public Security. The delegation is led by Inspector General of Police Moli Lal Bohara. This is the first time for a Nepali police delegation to pay an official visit to China. The two sides will exchange views on border area management during the visit. The police delegation will arrive in Beijing Sunday [15 May] via Bangkok.
